<br>
Mythic, at one time, was talking about having guild vaults in our up-coming guild houses.<br>
From my limited experience, the hard part about assaulting a keep, is getting the parts for a siege engine gathered up.  Wouldn't that be a great use for a guild vault?  Instead of a helter-skelter run to make and gather parts, we could just bank them in our guild house.  When the time comes, everyone heads for our house, we pass out the needed parts, and off we go to the battle!  <br>
Let's keep our fingers crossed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ufarmelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farmelle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.horsford.force9.co.uk/Icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/18/02 10:02:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1061.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.horsford.force9.co.uk/Photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thoughts on the future</span><hr size=1> Thats what I have been doing with Ali's vault.  I will try to keep at least 2 Ram Beaks in stock for the future, though it only takes me 5 mins to knock them up.  If they are needed then I can transfer them to people when they port out or before if its not in my play hours.<br>
<br>
